data.chText: 担忧；焦虑
data.enText: worry/anxiety

data.chText: 压力；重负；重压之下出现的问题（或担忧等）
data.enText: pressure on sb/sth because they have too much to do or manage, or sth very difficult to deal with; the problems, worry or anxiety that this produces

data.chText: 眼下他们的婚姻关系非常紧张。
data.enText: Their marriage is under great strain at the moment.

data.chText: 偿还这些债务对我们的财务状况形成了压力。
data.enText: These repayments are putting a strain on our finances.

data.chText: 你歇一下，我们来顶一会儿。
data.enText: Relax, and let us take the strain (= do things for you) .

data.chText: 运输部门无法应对临时增加这么多乘客所带来的紧张局面。
data.enText: The transport service cannot cope with the strain of so many additional passengers.

data.chText: 你要学会怎样应付公众人物生活的紧张和辛劳。
data.enText: You will learn to cope with the stresses and strains of public life.

data.chText: 我觉得这么长时间全神贯注挺累的。
data.enText: I found it a strain having to concentrate for so long.

data.chText: 物理压力
data.enText: physical pressure

data.chText: 压力；拉力；张力；应力
data.enText: the pressure that is put on sth when a physical force stretches, pushes, or pulls it

data.chText: 绳子给拉断了。
data.enText: The rope broke under the strain .

data.chText: 你要尽量不让肌肉和关节太吃力。
data.enText: You should try not to place too much strain on muscles and joints.

data.chText: 这块地承受不住大型建筑的压力。
data.enText: The ground here cannot take the strain of a large building.

data.chText: 这种缆索的断裂应变力为140公斤。
data.enText: The cable has a 140kg breaking strain (= it will break when it is stretched or pulled by a force greater than this) .

data.chText: 损伤
data.enText: injury

data.chText: 劳损；拉伤；扭伤
data.enText: an injury to a part of your body, such as a muscle, that is caused by using it too much or by twisting it

data.chText: 腿肚子 / 腹股沟 / 腿部拉伤
data.enText: a calf/groin/leg strain

data.chText: 肌肉劳损
data.enText: muscle strain

data.chText: 动植物 / 疾病种类
data.enText: type of plant/animal/disease

data.chText: （动、植物的）系，品系，品种；（疾病的）类型
data.enText: a particular type of plant or animal, or of a disease caused by bacteria, etc.

data.chText: 对这种毒药有抗药性的新品种蚊子
data.enText: a new strain of mosquitoes resistant to the poison

data.chText: 这种病有许多类型，这只是其中之一。
data.enText: This is only one of the many strains of the disease.

data.chText: 性格
data.enText: in sb's character

data.chText: 个性特点；性格倾向；禀性
data.enText: a particular tendency in the character of a person or group, or a quality in their manner

data.chText: 他这个人明显有一股势利小人的气味。
data.enText: He had a definite strain of snobbery in him.

data.chText: 音乐
data.enText: of music

data.chText: 乐曲；曲调；旋律
data.enText: the sound of music being played or sung

data.chText: 她能听见窗户里飘出的莫扎特的旋律。
data.enText: She could hear the strains of Mozart through the window.

data.chText: 损伤
data.enText: injure

data.chText: 损伤；拉伤；扭伤
data.enText: to injure yourself or part of your body by making it work too hard

data.chText: 拉伤肌肉
data.enText: to strain a muscle

data.chText: 尽力
data.enText: make effort

data.chText: 尽力；竭力；使劲
data.enText: to make an effort to do sth, using all your mental or physical strength

data.chText: 我竖起耳朵去听他们在说些什么。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: I strained my ears (= listened very hard) to catch what they were saying.

data.chText: 大家伸长了脖子想看一看这个陌生人。
data.enText: Necks were strained for a glimpse of the stranger.

data.chText: 人们翘首企足看发生了什么事。
data.enText: People were straining to see what was going on.

data.chText: 他冲出水面，使劲吸气。
data.enText: He burst to the surface, straining for air.

data.chText: 轻轻向左弯，不要用力。
data.enText: Bend gently to the left without straining.

data.chText: 使达到极限
data.enText: stretch to limit

data.chText: 过度使用；使不堪承受
data.enText: to try to make sth do more than it is able to do

data.chText: 游客突然涌入，城里的旅馆全都爆满。
data.enText: The sudden influx of visitors is straining hotels in the town to the limit.

data.chText: 他没完没了的抱怨让我们忍无可忍。
data.enText: His constant complaints were straining our patience.

data.chText: 这场争端使两国关系紧张起来。
data.enText: The dispute has strained relations between the two countries (= made them difficult) .

data.chText: 用力推 / 拉
data.enText: push/pull hard

data.chText: 用力推（或拉）；拉紧
data.enText: to push hard against sth; to pull hard on sth

data.chText: 她使劲挣了挣拴着她的绳子。
data.enText: She strained against the ropes that held her.

data.chText: 几条狗用力拽着皮带，急于要去公园。
data.enText: The dogs were straining at the leash , eager to get to the park.

data.chText: 过滤
data.enText: separate solid from liquid

data.chText: 滤；过滤
data.enText: to pour food, etc. through sth with very small holes in it, for example a sieve , in order to separate the solid part from the liquid part

data.chText: 把蔬菜放在漏筐里控控水。
data.enText: Use a colander to strain the vegetables.

data.chText: 滤掉多余的液体。
data.enText: Strain off any excess liquid.
strain at the leash

data.chText: 急于；迫不及待
data.enText: to want to do sth very much

data.chText: 跟所有年轻人一样，他也急于从家里出去。
data.enText: Like all youngsters, he's straining at the leash to leave home.
strain every nerve/sinew (to do sth)

data.chText: 竭尽全力（做某事）
data.enText: to try as hard as you can to do sth
creak under the strain

data.chText: 因负担过重而效率低下；由于压力过大而运转不灵
data.enText: if a system or service creaks under the strain , it cannot deal effectively with all the things it is expected to do or provide

data.text: injure ♦ wound ♦ hurt ♦ bruise ♦ maim ♦ sprain ♦ pull ♦ twist ♦ strain

data.chText: 以上各词主要指在事故中伤害、使受伤。
data.enText: These words all mean to harm yourself or sb else physically, especially in an accident.
injure

data.chText: 尤指在事故中伤害、使受伤：
data.enText: to harm yourself or sb else physically, especially in an accident

data.chText: 他打曲棍球时膝盖受了伤。
data.enText: He injured his knee playing hockey.

data.chText: 撞车事故中有三人受伤。
data.enText: Three people were injured in the crash.
wound

data.chText: 指使身体受伤，尤指用武器伤害：
data.enText: [often passive] ( rather formal ) to injure part of the body, especially by making a hole in the skin using a weapon

data.chText: 这次袭击中有50人受重伤。
data.enText: 50 people were seriously wounded in the attack.

data.chText: wound常指在战争中或在波及许多人的其他袭击中受伤。
data.enText: Wound is often used to talk about people being hurt in war or in other attacks which affect a lot of people.
hurt

data.chText: 指（使）疼痛、受伤：
data.enText: to cause physical pain to sb/yourself; to injure sb/yourself

data.chText: 你伤着自己了吗？
data.enText: Did you hurt yourself?

data.chText: 用hurt还是injure？
在事故中身体受伤可用hurt或injure，hurt强调引起的身体疼痛，injure强调身体部位受到某种程度的损伤。
data.enText: You can hurt or injure a part of the body in an accident. Hurt emphasizes the physical pain caused; injure emphasizes that the part of the body has been damaged in some way.
hurt or injure?
bruise

data.chText: 指摔伤、撞伤、（使）出现淤伤
data.enText: to make a blue, brown or purple mark (= a bruise) appear on the skin after sb has fallen or been hit; to develop a bruise
maim

data.chText: 指使残废、使受重伤
data.enText: ( rather formal ) to injure sb seriously, causing permanent damage to their body
sprain

data.chText: 扭伤（踝、腕、膝）
data.enText: to injure part of your body, especially your ankle, wrist or knee, by suddenly bending it in an awkward way, causing pain and swelling
pull

data.chText: 拉伤，扭伤（肌肉等）
data.enText: to damage a muscle, etc., by using too much force
twist

data.chText: 扭伤（踝、腕、膝）
data.enText: to suddenly bend a part of your body, especially your ankle, wrist or knee, in an awkward way, causing an injury that involves pain and swelling

data.chText: 用sprain还是twist？
sprain作名词表示踝、腕、膝扭伤引起疼痛或肿胀，作动词表示使踝、腕、膝扭伤；twist作动词表示扭伤踝、腕、膝。
data.enText: A sprain is an injury to your ankle, wrist or knee that causes pain and swelling; to sprain your ankle/wrist/knee is to injure it in this way. To twist your ankle/wrist/knee is to do the action (= to suddenly bend it in an awkward way) that causes the injury.
sprain or twist?
strain

data.chText: 指损伤、拉伤、扭伤：
data.enText: to injure yourself or part of your body by making it work too hard

data.chText: 别在光线差的地方看书把眼睛给伤了。
data.enText: Don't strain your eyes by reading in poor light.
to injure/hurt/strain yourself
to injure/hurt/sprain/pull/strain a muscle
to injure/hurt/sprain/twist your ankle/foot/knee
to injure/hurt/sprain your wrist/hand
to injure/hurt/strain your back/shoulder/eyes
to injure/hurt your spine/neck
to be badly/seriously/severely/slightly injured/wounded/hurt/bruised/maimed/sprained
to be slightly injured/wounded/hurt/bruised/sprained

data.chText: 以上各词均指生活上的心理压力、精神紧张。
data.enText: These are all words for the feelings of anxiety caused by the problems in sb's life.
pressure

data.chText: 指为达到某一目标或有某种行为表现而产生的心理压力、紧张：
data.enText: difficulties and feelings of anxiety that are caused by the need to achieve sth or to behave in a particular way

data.chText: 由于工作紧张她不能出席。
data.enText: She was unable to attend because of the pressures of work.
stress

data.chText: 指因生活问题引起的精神压力、心理负担、紧张：
data.enText: pressure or anxiety caused by the problems in sb's life

data.chText: 与精神压力有关的疾病
data.enText: stress-related illnesses

data.chText: 用pressure还是stress？
承受精神压力常用suffer from stress，而pressure可指造成压力（stress）的事物。
data.enText: It is common to say that sb is suffering from stress , while pressure may be the thing that causes stress .
pressure or stress?
tension

data.chText: 指情绪上的紧张、烦躁：
data.enText: a feeling of anxiety and stress that makes it impossible to relax

data.chText: 神经紧张
data.enText: nervous tension
strain

data.chText: 指压力、重负、重压之下出现的问题、担忧：
data.enText: pressure on sb/sth because they have too much to do or manage; the problems, worry or anxiety that this produces

data.chText: 我觉得照料四个孩子挺累的。
data.enText: I found it a strain looking after four children.
to cause stress/tension/strain
cope with/deal with/handle the pressure/stress/tension/strain
to relieve/ease the pressure/stress/tension/strain
to be suffering from stress/tension
to be under pressure/stress/strain
considerable pressure/stress/tension/strain

means: 重压之下出现的问题(或担忧等)

ex.chText: 你可以通过做运动来减压。
ex.enText: You can do some exercises to relieve tension.

ex.chText: 这次会谈大大缓和了紧张局面。
ex.enText: The talk lessened the tension greatly.

ex.chText: 学生和教职员工之间的关系逐渐紧张起来。
ex.enText: Tension developed between the students and faculty.

ex.chText: 头痛可能是由颈部肌肉紧张导致的。
ex.enText: Headaches may be caused by tension in the neck muscles.

synonyms.bx: 主要指精神、心理上的紧张，也指人与人或国与国之间的紧张关系，或某物被过度拉伸的程度或状态。

ex.chText: 这轮胎太硬，要减少一点压力。
ex.enText: The tyre is too hard; reduce the pressure a bit.

ex.chText: 她的身体被工作压力压垮了。
ex.enText: Her health collapsed under the pressure of work.

ex.chText: 我们应对他施加更大的压力。
ex.enText: We must bring more pressure to bear on him.

ex.chText: 她能妥善应付生活压力。
ex.enText: She was able to cope well with the pressures of life.

synonyms.bx: 多指由气体或液体产生的压力，或某事物所产生的压力或影响力，包括工作或生活中的压力。

ex.chText: 这根柱子承受了整个结构的压力。
ex.enText: This post takes the strain of the whole structure.

ex.chText: 她现在心情紧张，因为她的小孩病了。
ex.enText: She's under a lot of strain at the moment because her child's ill.

ex.chText: 工作量过大使雇员产生很严重的焦虑情绪。
ex.enText: Too much work put a severe strain on employees.

synonyms.bx: 指物体所承受的张力或拉力，也指因外界压力而造成的身心和情绪等方面的焦虑或压抑。

ex.chText: 高跟鞋会对脚踝产生很大的压力。
ex.enText: Shoes with high heels put great stress on ankles.

ex.chText: 苏珊被考试的压力压垮了。
ex.enText: Susan was completely weighed down by the stress of examinations.

ex.chText: 新工作的压力使他患上了胃溃疡。
ex.enText: The stress from the new job caused him to suffer from gastric ulcers.

synonyms.bx: 指施加于物体、能使其损坏或变形的压力或应力；也指精神压力或心理负担，侧重于一种长期的忧虑。

data.chText: 急于；迫不及待
data.enText: to want to do sth very much

data.chText: 跟所有年轻人一样，他也急于从家里出去。
data.enText: Like all youngsters, he's straining at the leash to leave home.
strain every nerve/sinew (to do sth)

data.chText: 竭尽全力（做某事）
data.enText: to try as hard as you can to do sth
creak under the strain

data.chText: 因负担过重而效率低下；由于压力过大而运转不灵
data.enText: if a system or service creaks under the strain , it cannot deal effectively with all the things it is expected to do or provide

tr: the act of singing
example: with a shout and a song they marched up to the gates

tr: an intense or violent exertion
an effortful attempt to attain a goal
the general meaning or substance of an utterance
example: although I disagreed with him I could follow the tenor of his argument

tr: a succession of notes forming a distinctive sequence
example: she was humming an air from Beethoven

tr: a special variety of domesticated animals within a species
example: he experimented on a particular breed of white rats
he created a new strain of sheep

tr: (biology) a group of organisms within a species that differ in trivial ways from similar groups
example: a new strain of microorganisms

tr: (physics) deformation of a physical body under the action of applied forces
injury to a muscle (often caused by overuse)
results in swelling and pain
(psychology) nervousness resulting from mental stress
example: his responsibilities were a constant strain
the mental strain of staying alert hour after hour was too much for him

tr: difficulty that causes worry or emotional tension
example: she endured the stresses and strains of life
he presided over the economy during the period of the greatest stress and danger"- R.J.Samuelso

tr: cause to be tense and uneasy or nervous or anxious
example: he got a phone call from his lawyer that tensed him up

tr: alter the shape of (something) by stress
example: His body was deformed by leprosy

tr: to exert much effort or energy
example: straining our ears to hear

tr: use to the utmost
exert vigorously or to full capacity
example: He really extended himself when he climbed Kilimanjaro
Don't strain your mind too much

tr: rub through a strainer or process in an electric blender
example: puree the vegetables for the baby

tr: remove by passing through a filter
example: filter out the impurities

tr: separate by passing through a sieve or other straining device to separate out coarser elements
example: sift the flour

tr: become stretched or tense or taut
"the rope strained when the weight was attached"
example: the bodybuilder's neck muscles tense

tr: test the limits of
example: You are trying my patience!

value.def: If strain is put on an organization or system, it has to do more than it is able to do.

example.ex: The prison service is already under considerable strain...
example.tran: 监狱系统已经承受了巨大的压力。

example.ex: The vast expansion in secondary education is putting an enormous strain on the system.
example.tran: 中等教育的大幅扩张正对该系统造成巨大压力。

example.ex: ...the credit crunch caused by strains on the banking system.
example.tran: 银行系统在多重压力之下紧缩信贷

value.def: To strain something means to make it do more than it is able to do.

example.ex: The volume of scheduled flights is straining the air traffic control system...
example.tran: 定期航班的数量正让空中交通指挥系统不堪重负。

example.ex: Resources will be further strained by new demands for housing.
example.tran: 资源将因新的住房需求而变得更紧张。

value.def: Strain is a state of worry and tension caused by a difficult situation.

example.ex: She was tired and under great strain.
example.tran: 她身心疲惫，压力很大。

example.ex: ...the stresses and strains of a busy and demanding career.
example.tran: 忙碌而辛苦的工作带来的巨大压力

value.def: If you say that a situation is a strain, you mean that it makes you worried and tense.

example.ex: I sometimes find it a strain to be responsible for the mortgage.
example.tran: 我有时觉得背负这笔抵押贷款很有压力。

value.tran: 带来压力的情况;造成紧张的因素

value.def: Strain is a force that pushes, pulls, or stretches something in a way that may damage it.

example.ex: Place your hands under your buttocks to take some of the strain off your back...
example.tran: 将手放在臀部下面，减轻背部的一些压力。

example.ex: A build-up of strain on a section of the San Andreas Fault has been detected.
example.tran: 已经勘测到圣安德烈亚斯断层的其中一处所承受的拉力在增强。

value.tran: 应力;张力;拉力;作用力;压力

value.def: Strain is an injury to a muscle in your body, caused by using the muscle too much or twisting it.

example.ex: Avoid muscle strain by warming up with slow jogging.
example.tran: 先慢跑热热身，免得拉伤肌肉。

example.ex: ...a groin strain.
example.tran: 腹股沟拉伤

value.def: If you strain a muscle, you injure it by using it too much or twisting it.

example.ex: He strained his back during a practice session.
example.tran: 他在一次锻炼中扭伤了背部。

value.def: If you strain to do something, you make a great effort to do it when it is difficult to do.

example.ex: I had to strain to hear...
example.tran: 我不得不使劲去听。

example.ex: Several thousand supporters strained to catch a glimpse of the new president...
example.tran: 几千名支持者翘首企盼能一睹新总统的风采。

example.ex: They strained their eyes, but saw nothing.
example.tran: 他们瞪大了双眼，但什么也没看到。

value.tran: 努力做;竭力做;费力做事

value.def: When you strain food, you separate the liquid part of it from the solid parts.

example.ex: Strain the stock and put it back into the pan.
example.tran: 滤出原汁，将它放回到平底锅中。

value.tran: 过滤;滤掉(食物中)的液体

value.def: You can use strain to refer to a particular quality in someone's character, remarks, or work.

example.ex: There was a strain of bitterness in his voice.
example.tran: 他的声音听起来有些愤愤不平。

example.ex: ...this cynical strain in the book.
example.tran: 该书中这种愤世嫉俗的意味

value.def: A strain of a germ, plant, or other organism is a particular type of it.

example.ex: Every year new strains of influenza develop.
example.tran: 每年都有新的流感病毒出现。

example.ex: ...a particularly beautiful strain of Swiss pansies.
example.tran: 一种格外美丽的瑞士三色堇

value.tran: (病菌的)类型;(植物或其他有机物的)系，品系，品种

value.def: If you hear the strains of music, you hear music being played.

example.ex: She could hear the tinny strains of a chamber orchestra.
example.tran: 她能听见室内管弦乐队尖细的旋律。
